              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The NaI(Tl) crystals used were 1.5 inches in",
                "diameter by 1.5 inches long."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "6-C-13",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.6
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The two targets used were 7 and 16",
                "keV thick at 1.7 MeV and were composed of carbon,",
                "enriched to 60 percent C13, deposited on a tantalum",
                "backing."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The gamma rays were produced by bombarding C13",
                "targets with protons. The protons were analyzed by",
                "either an electrostatic or a magnetic analyzer set to",
                "give an energy resolution of 0.1 to 0.2 percent. At",
                "each resonance, before observing the pulse-height",
                "spectrum, an excitation curve was run in order to",
                "obtain the maximum intensity and also to be sure that",
                "the observed radiation was characteristic of the",
                "resonance."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "With the exception of the 8.90(1.47)- and 8.98(1.55)-",
                "MeV resonance levels and the recalculated reduced",
                "widths, the table is essentially Table III in",
                "reference C1645 (J,PR,85,197,1952). Consequently,",
                "only these two data points were compiled in order to",
                "avoid duplication."
              ]
            }
          ],
